      "alt": "Here is a detailed alternative text description for the image image_6fb048.png:\n\nAlternative Text Description\nA data visualization dashboard titled \"POSTERIOR DISTRIBUTION\" displayed on a dark background. The image tracks probability predictions across four hypothetical timeframes (H1 through H4) regarding a reopening date.\n\n1. Probability Breakdown Bar\nAt the top, a horizontal segmented progress bar visualizes the current probability distribution for each hypothesis:\n\nH1 (Green): Reopens by 2026-09-30 (2%)\n\nH2 (Blue): Reopens 2026-10-01 to 2027-03-31 (2%)\n\nH3 (Orange): Reopens 2027-04-01 to 2027-12-31 (81%, dominant segment)\n\nH4 (Red): Not reopened by 2027-12-31 (16%)\n\nDirectly below the bar, a large orange text metric reads:\n\nE[days from 2026-05-03] = 527.12 (2027-10-12)\n\n2. Historical Trend Line Graph\nA line chart below tracks how these probabilities have changed over time from early May to mid-June. The y-axis measures probability from 0% to 100%, and the x-axis shows dates (labeled with repeating markers like 05-05, 05-07, 05-10, and 06-12).\n\nH3 (Orange Line): Starts near 45% in early May, steadily climbs with some volatility, peaks around 80% in mid-May, dips slightly, and ends at its highest point near 81% in mid-June.\n\nH4 (Red Line): Fluctuates between 10% and 40% throughout the period, finishing with a downward trend at 16%.\n\nH2 (Blue Line) & H1 (Green Line): Both start with minor activity in early May (H2 peaks briefly around 38%), but both flatten out near 0% to 2% for the remainder of the timeline.",
